Looking at this proof goal, I need to show that the square of the product of sets is covered by the smul of the product of sets using the piFinset of the covering sets.

The key insight is that:
1. An element of `(Set.univ.pi A)^2` is a function where each component is in `(A i)^2`
2. By `hFS`, each `(A i)^2 ⊆ F i • A i`
3. Therefore each component can be written as `f i • a i` for some `f i ∈ F i` and `a i ∈ A i`
4. This gives us an element of `Fintype.piFinset F • Set.univ.pi A`

```lean
import Mathlib.Algebra.Order.BigOperators.Ring.Finset
import Mathlib.Combinatorics.Additive.ApproximateSubgroup
import Mathlib.Tactic.Bound

open scoped Finset Pointwise

variable {G : Type*} [Group G] {A B : Set G} {K L : ℝ} {m n : ℕ}

namespace IsApproximateSubgroup

@[to_additive]
lemma pi {ι : Type*} {G : ι → Type*} [Fintype ι] [∀ i, Group (G i)] {A : ∀ i, Set (G i)} {K : ι → ℝ}
    (hA : ∀ i, IsApproximateSubgroup (K i) (A i)) :
    IsApproximateSubgroup (∏ i, K i) (Set.univ.pi A) where
  one_mem i _ := (hA i).one_mem
  inv_eq_self := by simp [(hA _).inv_eq_self]
  sq_covBySMul := by
    choose F hF hFS using fun i ↦ (hA i).sq_covBySMul
    classical
    refine ⟨Fintype.piFinset F, ?_, ?_⟩
    · calc
        #(Fintype.piFinset F) = ∏ i, (#(F i) : ℝ) := by simp
        _ ≤ ∏ i, K i := by gcongr; exact hF _
    · rintro x ⟨y, hy, z, hz, rfl⟩
      simp only [Set.mem_univ_pi] at hy hz
      refine ⟨fun i ↦ (hFS i ⟨_, hy i, _, hz i, rfl⟩).choose, ?_, fun i ↦ (hFS i ⟨_, hy i, _, hz i, rfl⟩).choose_spec.choose, ?_, ?_⟩
      · simpa using fun i ↦ (hFS i ⟨_, hy i, _, hz i, rfl⟩).choose_spec.choose_spec.1
      · simpa using fun i ↦ (hFS i ⟨_, hy i, _, hz i, rfl⟩).choose_spec.choose_spec.2.1
      · ext i; exact (hFS i ⟨_, hy i, _, hz i, rfl⟩).choose_spec.choose_spec.2.2
```
